---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="About — RelayLaunch"
  description="RelayLaunch was founded by Victor David Medina — cloud engineer, USMC veteran, and small business advocate. Enterprise infrastructure applied at small business scale."
>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ HERO -->
  <section class="section hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">About RelayLaunch</span>
      <h1 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(32px, 5vw, 52px); max-width: 700px;">
        Enterprise infrastructure. Small business focus. No fluff.
      </h1>
      <p class="section-sub" style="max-width: 600px;">
        RelayLaunch was built on a simple observation: small businesses are drowning in
        disconnected tools and paying consultants who hand them a slide deck and disappear.
        There's a better way.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ FOUNDER -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="founder-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="section-eyebrow">The Founder</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Victor David Medina</h2>
          <p class="founder-role">Founder, RelayLaunch LLC</p>

          <div class="bio-block">
            <p>
              I've spent my career building infrastructure that handles complexity — enterprise
              cloud systems, cross-border operations integrations, and large-scale platform migrations.
              At ezCater I managed a 1,000-user Expensify + NetSuite/Namely integration that processes
              thousands of transactions daily. At Blue Matter I ran cross-border post-merger integrations
              with full regulatory compliance.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
              What I kept seeing was that the same problems plaguing Fortune 500 migrations were
              also destroying small businesses — just at a different scale. A local spa shouldn't
              need to pay $342/month for five tools that don't talk to each other. A local contractor
              shouldn't lose 8 hours a week to manual follow-ups that a workflow could handle.
            </p>
            <p style="margin-top: 16px;">
              RelayLaunch is the bridge between enterprise-level systems thinking and the small
              businesses that need it most but can rarely afford it. The same methodology that
              works at 1,000 users works at 10. It just needs to be sized appropriately.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div class="card credentials-card">
            <p class="section-eyebrow" style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Background</p>
            <div class="cred-list">
              <div class="cred-item">
                <div class="cred-icon">🎖️</div>
                <div>
                  <strong>USMC Sergeant (E-5) — Honorable Discharge</strong>
                  <p>Structured execution and mission completion aren't aspirational values. They're operational defaults.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="cred-item">
                <div class="cred-icon">☁️</div>
                <div>
                  <strong>Cloud Engineering</strong>
                  <p>DNS, CDN, CI/CD pipelines, security headers, CSP — Fortune 500 infrastructure disciplines applied to small business systems.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="cred-item">
                <div class="cred-icon">🏢</div>
                <div>
                  <strong>Enterprise Operations</strong>
                  <p>ezCater (1,000-user integrations, $1B+ transaction volume) · Blue Matter (cross-border post-merger systems) · Regulatory compliance experience.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="cred-item">
                <div class="cred-icon">⚙️</div>
                <div>
                  <strong>Proprietary Automation Methodology</strong>
                  <p>Custom-built workflow pipelines — not off-the-shelf templates. Every workflow is designed for the client's specific business logic.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ MISSION -->
  <section class="section mission-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="mission-grid">
        <div>
          <span class="section-eyebrow">The Mission</span>
          <h2 class="section-title">Be the connector small businesses never had.</h2>
          <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 16px;">
            Most consultants deliver documents. Most web designers deliver websites.
            Neither of those is enough anymore. Small businesses need someone who can
            see the whole system — and actually build it.
          </p>
          <p style="color: var(--color-muted); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.7; margin-top: 16px;">
            RelayLaunch connects the tools, automates the workflows, builds the digital
            presence, and stays in the work long enough to make sure it runs. The goal
            is simple: you became a business owner to run your business — not to be an
            IT department, a content creator, and a data analyst all at once.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="values-list">
          <div class="value-item">
            <span class="value-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Build, don't advise.</strong>
              <p>Deliverables are working systems — not slide decks or strategy documents that gather dust.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="value-item">
            <span class="value-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Honest scoping.</strong>
              <p>You get a realistic timeline and clear deliverables upfront. No scope creep surprises.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="value-item">
            <span class="value-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Infrastructure first.</strong>
              <p>DNS, CDN, hosting, CI/CD, security — handled correctly from day one, not bolted on later.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="value-item">
            <span class="value-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <strong>You run your business.</strong>
              <p>Every system we build should free up your time, not create a new dependency on us.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ WHY DIFFERENT -->
  <section class="section" style="background: var(--color-surface);">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">The Difference</span>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">Not a web design shop.</h2>

      <div class="compare-table-wrap">
        <table class="rl-table compare-table">
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>What Most Shops Do</th>
              <th class="green-header">What RelayLaunch Does</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Build a website and hand it over</td>
              <td>Build unified infrastructure: website + automation + email + social + dashboard</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Use templates and page builders</td>
              <td>Custom-coded in Astro + Tailwind CSS — no templates, no page builders</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Bolt on automation as an upsell</td>
              <td>Automation built in from day one — it's the core, not an add-on</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Host on shared servers</td>
              <td>Deployed on Cloudflare Pages — CDN, DDoS protection, 99.99% uptime, $0/month</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Hand you login credentials and disappear</td>
              <td>Daily briefings in your Slack dashboard — your business reports to you</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Charge $300–500/month for ongoing tools</td>
              <td>Replace $300–500/month in tools with $50–80/month in infrastructure</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>DNS? CDN? CI/CD? Not their problem.</td>
              <td>Infrastructure-first: every layer handled at cloud-engineering standards</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════ CTA -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 class="section-title">Ready to work together?</h2>
      <p class="section-sub" style="margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 32px;">
        Start with a conversation. Tell us where you are and what you're trying to build.
      </p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary">Start a Project →</a>
        <a href="/case-studies/hrc" class="btn-secondary">See the HRC Case Study</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .hero { padding-top: 80px; }

  .founder-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 56px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .founder-role {
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--color-green);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 28px;
  }

  .bio-block p { font-size: 16px; color: var(--color-muted); line-height: 1.75; }

  .credentials-card { padding: 28px; }

  .cred-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 24px; }

  .cred-item { display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: flex-start; }
  .cred-icon { font-size: 20px; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: 2px; }
  .cred-item strong { display: block; font-size: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .cred-item p { font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.6; }

  /* ── Mission ── */
  .mission-section { background: var(--color-surface); }

  .mission-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 56px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .values-list { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 24px; }

  .value-item { display: flex; gap: 16px; align-items: flex-start; }
  .value-num {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 1.5px;
    color: var(--color-green);
    margin-top: 3px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .value-item strong { display: block; font-size: 15px; margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .value-item p { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; }

  /* ── Compare table ── */
  .compare-table-wrap { overflow-x: auto; }
  .compare-table { min-width: 600px; }

  .compare-table .green-header { color: var(--color-green); }
  .compare-table tbody tr td:nth-child(2) { color: var(--color-text); }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .founder-grid, .mission-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 40px; }
  }
</style>
